\f0\fs20 \cf0 The real world relevance of [](#prop2)(ii) depends crucially on whether firms do actually liquidate under such conditions. Evidence in the home mortgage market suggests they do. Lenders are more frequently and quickly transferred ownership of houses from delinquent borrowers with little to no equity in their homes[#Ambrose1998,Pennington-Cross2010]. Borrowers' quick surrender may be especially likely when bankruptcy incurs a personal cost, such as lost time. See also [](#fnm:fn1) for a discussion on the likelihood of voluntary liquidation and the entrepreneur's original intent to liquidate.}

